1
00:00:04,571 --> 00:00:06,071
If you want to get her to study,

2
00:00:06,072 --> 00:00:08,240
you'll be better off throwing away
the textbooks altogether.

3
00:00:08,241 --> 00:00:09,241
Excuse me?

4
00:00:09,242 --> 00:00:11,910
While you're here,
only do things that you think are fun.

5
00:00:11,911 --> 00:00:12,911
What's with that guy?

6
00:00:12,912 --> 00:00:16,081
<i>He's got a super naive mindset,
but is he all right?</i>

7
00:00:16,082 --> 00:00:17,082
Tatsuki.

8
00:00:17,083 --> 00:00:18,550
‎PREVIOUSLY ON <i>‎TATSUKI: TOO KIND FOR SCHOOL</i>

9
00:00:18,551 --> 00:00:19,652
I don't

10
00:00:20,820 --> 00:00:22,021
want to go to school.

11
00:00:22,022 --> 00:00:23,390
I think Ayaka couldn't

12
00:00:23,957 --> 00:00:25,758
bring herself to express her true feelings

13
00:00:25,759 --> 00:00:28,060
because her mother is so important to her.

14
00:00:28,061 --> 00:00:29,662
I was always

15
00:00:30,930 --> 00:00:33,333
a little too relieved whenever…

16
00:00:34,467 --> 00:00:35,834
you went to school, huh?

17
00:00:35,835 --> 00:00:37,137
I'm sorry.

18
00:00:38,738 --> 00:00:40,139
- Hello?
<i>- Tatsuki.</i>

19
00:00:40,140 --> 00:00:41,708
Sora jumped.

20
00:00:43,043 --> 00:00:43,943
What?

21
00:00:48,248 --> 00:00:49,249
How's Sora?

22
00:00:53,720 --> 00:00:54,687
Is he in there?

23
00:00:55,488 --> 00:00:56,523
Wait.

24
00:00:57,490 --> 00:00:58,591
It's all right.

25
00:00:59,793 --> 00:01:02,595
- But he jumped--
- He's not in a critical condition.

26
00:01:04,197 --> 00:01:05,065
So just leave.

27
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:08,334
Now.

28
00:01:32,459 --> 00:01:34,260
Tatsuki.

29
00:01:39,532 --> 00:01:40,600
He's sleeping.

30
00:01:44,971 --> 00:01:46,705
What? What is it?

31
00:01:46,706 --> 00:01:47,940
It's time for the meeting.

32
00:01:47,941 --> 00:01:49,775
- Meeting?
- Yeah.

33
00:01:49,776 --> 00:01:50,610
Okay.

34
00:01:51,277 --> 00:01:54,213
All right,
let's begin this week's meeting.

35
00:01:54,214 --> 00:01:56,048
- Okay.
- Okay.

36
00:01:56,049 --> 00:01:57,549
First up, Tuesday.

37
00:01:57,550 --> 00:02:00,252
There's a plan to go see the movie <i>Mario,</i>

38
00:02:00,253 --> 00:02:01,520
but is everyone done signing up?

39
00:02:01,521 --> 00:02:03,155
- I'll go too.
- Okay.

40
00:02:03,156 --> 00:02:05,991
- I'll sign up too.
- Let's watch a romantic comedy.

41
00:02:05,992 --> 00:02:08,093
- Romantic comedy?
- I have an idea for the next

42
00:02:08,094 --> 00:02:09,294
- training camp.
- Training camp?

43
00:02:09,295 --> 00:02:11,730
I want to eat paella this week.

44
00:02:11,731 --> 00:02:13,866
- Paella?
- Yes, paella.

45
00:02:13,867 --> 00:02:15,734
Paella!

46
00:02:15,735 --> 00:02:19,404
Hold on, we're still discussing the movie.
We'll talk about the paella later.

47
00:02:19,405 --> 00:02:21,473
We hold a meeting like this every week

48
00:02:21,474 --> 00:02:22,909
to decide on various plans.

49
00:02:23,510 --> 00:02:25,310
Do I need to take charge or anything?

50
00:02:25,311 --> 00:02:26,411
No need.

51
00:02:26,412 --> 00:02:28,381
We just need to watch over them.

52
00:02:28,948 --> 00:02:30,416
Everything works out all right?

53
00:02:30,984 --> 00:02:33,051
They won't follow plans made by adults,

54
00:02:33,052 --> 00:02:36,155
but they'll stick to the ones
they decided on themselves.

55
00:02:36,156 --> 00:02:37,456
- I see.
- Next.

56
00:02:37,457 --> 00:02:40,993
What's the plan for Thursday's
Activity Day at the community center?

57
00:02:40,994 --> 00:02:42,427
- Tag.
- Dodgeball.

58
00:02:42,428 --> 00:02:43,662
- Tag?
- Basketball!

59
00:02:43,663 --> 00:02:45,564
- Yeah, basketball.
- Paella.

60
00:02:45,565 --> 00:02:47,332
- Dodgeball?
- Enough with the paella.

61
00:02:47,333 --> 00:02:49,935
- Yeah, I want to do that too.
- Okay, let's vote.

62
00:02:49,936 --> 00:02:51,436
Who wants to play tag?

63
00:02:51,437 --> 00:02:54,139
- Me.
- Who wants to play basketball?

64
00:02:54,140 --> 00:02:56,308
- Me.
- What?

65
00:02:56,309 --> 00:02:57,709
Hold on, guys.

66
00:02:57,710 --> 00:02:59,044
You can only vote once.

67
00:02:59,045 --> 00:03:00,479
We're not doing that.

68
00:03:00,480 --> 00:03:03,549
- I vote for dodgeball.
- I want to eat paella.

69
00:03:03,550 --> 00:03:06,419
- Who wants to do trampoline?
- I think it's a new applicant.

70
00:03:07,453 --> 00:03:08,655
All right.

71
00:03:10,890 --> 00:03:11,724
Mr. Tatsuki.

72
00:03:12,292 --> 00:03:13,425
Hello.

73
00:03:13,426 --> 00:03:15,028
- Nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

74
00:03:15,595 --> 00:03:16,429
Say hello.

75
00:03:17,864 --> 00:03:19,831
Hello, I'm Saku Sugitani.

76
00:03:19,832 --> 00:03:20,934
Hello.

77
00:03:22,068 --> 00:03:24,504
- Please sit.
- Thank you.

78
00:03:30,143 --> 00:03:32,711
He's currently a fifth grader
in elementary school,

79
00:03:32,712 --> 00:03:34,279
but starting around mid-April,

80
00:03:34,280 --> 00:03:36,548
he started taking days off of school.

81
00:03:36,549 --> 00:03:39,852
After the long holiday break,
he told me he doesn't want to go back.

82
00:03:41,087 --> 00:03:42,589
Did something happen at school?

83
00:03:44,691 --> 00:03:45,792
Not really.

84
00:03:46,960 --> 00:03:49,829
He doesn't seem to be having
any problems with his friends.

85
00:03:51,331 --> 00:03:52,999
You just don't want to go to school?

86
00:03:54,400 --> 00:03:55,602
It's a drag.

87
00:03:56,536 --> 00:03:57,670
A drag, huh.

88
00:03:58,238 --> 00:03:59,572
Yeah, school is such a drag.

89
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:01,074
I totally get it.

90
00:04:02,342 --> 00:04:04,810
- Mr. Tatsuki.
- What?

91
00:04:04,811 --> 00:04:07,846
I happened to learn about Yukanai online.

92
00:04:07,847 --> 00:04:11,350
I thought that letting children
be independent and free

93
00:04:11,351 --> 00:04:13,852
might be the right approach
for my son right now.

94
00:04:13,853 --> 00:04:17,190
Yes, everyone here is certainly
doing what they want.

95
00:04:17,957 --> 00:04:20,425
When I asked him about it,
he said he wanted to come.

96
00:04:20,426 --> 00:04:21,494
I see.

97
00:04:23,429 --> 00:04:24,764
Do you play soccer?

98
00:04:28,301 --> 00:04:30,103
You like sports in general, right?

99
00:04:31,437 --> 00:04:32,272
Kind of…

100
00:04:33,439 --> 00:04:34,706
- Yeah.
- I see.

101
00:04:34,707 --> 00:04:36,542
He's pretty good with his studies too.

102
00:04:37,110 --> 00:04:40,413
Whoa, no way.
You're definitely popular, huh?

103
00:04:41,014 --> 00:04:42,714
- You are, huh?
- Mr. Tatsuki.

104
00:04:42,715 --> 00:04:44,082
- What?
- Let's not say that.

105
00:04:44,083 --> 00:04:46,952
- Why? He's so impressive.
- But still…

106
00:04:46,953 --> 00:04:49,821
- There's no way he's not popular.
- That's not the issue.

107
00:04:49,822 --> 00:04:51,157
Your turn to serve.

108
00:04:51,958 --> 00:04:54,160
- Where did it go?
- Are you serious?

109
00:04:55,595 --> 00:04:58,030
Let's play soccer.

110
00:04:58,031 --> 00:04:58,865
Yeah.

111
00:05:00,600 --> 00:05:03,235
We're going to play soccer now,
wanna join us?

112
00:05:03,236 --> 00:05:04,203
It'll be out in the yard.

113
00:05:08,708 --> 00:05:10,142
I'm okay right now.

114
00:05:10,143 --> 00:05:11,410
Okay.

115
00:05:11,411 --> 00:05:13,179
Come join us when you feel like it.

116
00:05:14,514 --> 00:05:15,348
Okay.

117
00:05:16,282 --> 00:05:17,582
- Let's go.
- Yeah.

118
00:05:17,583 --> 00:05:19,318
- Nice, nice.
- Yeah.

119
00:05:19,319 --> 00:05:20,653
- Let's go.
- Yeah.

120
00:05:27,460 --> 00:05:29,562
You can use anything here
however you like.

121
00:05:32,432 --> 00:05:34,400
Hey, let's play Bomb Busters.

122
00:05:37,337 --> 00:05:38,737
Okay.

123
00:05:38,738 --> 00:05:39,939
Let's play next time.

124
00:05:40,640 --> 00:05:41,641
Gaku, let's play this.

125
00:05:48,348 --> 00:05:50,049
What?

126
00:05:50,850 --> 00:05:52,951
What happened?

127
00:05:52,952 --> 00:05:54,153
- I'm sorry.
- What happened?

128
00:05:54,787 --> 00:05:55,721
I'm sorry.

129
00:05:55,722 --> 00:05:57,056
- Are you all right?
- Yeah.

130
00:05:57,657 --> 00:05:59,491
I'm sorry.

131
00:05:59,492 --> 00:06:00,326
Thank you.

132
00:06:00,827 --> 00:06:03,628
- Were you replacing the books?
- Yeah.

133
00:06:03,629 --> 00:06:05,097
Professor Mikumo

134
00:06:05,098 --> 00:06:07,266
brought us a bunch of old books
the other day.

135
00:06:11,571 --> 00:06:12,872
Do you like history?

136
00:06:14,273 --> 00:06:15,108
No…

137
00:06:16,242 --> 00:06:19,779
I don't know much about history.

138
00:06:20,646 --> 00:06:22,315
Are there any Sengoku warlords you like?

139
00:06:26,252 --> 00:06:29,122
- Nobunaga.
- Oh, I know a little about him.

140
00:06:30,523 --> 00:06:32,224
Who's this man?

141
00:06:32,225 --> 00:06:33,159
TALES OF THE STRONGEST SENGOKU WARLORDS

142
00:06:33,726 --> 00:06:34,694
Kuroda Kanbei.

143
00:06:35,995 --> 00:06:38,064
Wow, you really know a lot!

144
00:06:44,370 --> 00:06:46,038
You can take that home.

145
00:06:46,973 --> 00:06:48,640
- Really?
- Yeah.

146
00:06:48,641 --> 00:06:50,376
I'm sure no one else will read it.

147
00:06:58,851 --> 00:07:00,119
I've got a good idea.

148
00:07:04,957 --> 00:07:07,225
- All right.
- What are you doing?

149
00:07:07,226 --> 00:07:08,961
I'm making a collage.

150
00:07:10,062 --> 00:07:11,564
- A collage?
- Yup.

151
00:07:12,331 --> 00:07:16,435
You just cut out images that you like

152
00:07:16,436 --> 00:07:18,137
and paste them together.

153
00:07:19,972 --> 00:07:22,975
By the way, those are collages
made by another student.

154
00:07:24,944 --> 00:07:26,212
Wow.

155
00:07:27,914 --> 00:07:28,748
Try it out.

156
00:07:36,989 --> 00:07:39,524
Which one should I choose?

157
00:07:39,525 --> 00:07:40,393
SOCCER MANIA

158
00:07:50,303 --> 00:07:52,671
Hey, can you help me reach the top of

159
00:07:52,672 --> 00:07:54,740
- the bookshelf--
- Once you cut that out, paste it on here.

160
00:07:55,942 --> 00:07:56,776
- Um…
- How?

161
00:07:57,710 --> 00:07:59,878
- However you want to.
- Can you hear me?

162
00:07:59,879 --> 00:08:03,281
It's too high, and I can't reach it so…

163
00:08:03,282 --> 00:08:04,983
- Ms. Shizuku.
- I'll do this one.

164
00:08:04,984 --> 00:08:06,919
Can you bring more old magazines?

165
00:08:07,987 --> 00:08:09,722
Go get them yourself.

166
00:08:10,923 --> 00:08:11,757
What was that for?

167
00:08:14,193 --> 00:08:17,129
- Mr. Tatsuki.
- Just call me Tatsuki.

168
00:08:18,297 --> 00:08:21,300
- You have to be nicer to women.
- What?

169
00:08:22,068 --> 00:08:23,835
Oh, you mean about Ms. Shizuku?

170
00:08:23,836 --> 00:08:25,370
Yeah. She was mad.

171
00:08:25,371 --> 00:08:27,907
What? She was mad?

172
00:08:28,875 --> 00:08:29,842
Really?

173
00:08:31,444 --> 00:08:32,712
You're so oblivious.

174
00:08:34,113 --> 00:08:35,414
I get that a lot.

175
00:08:36,749 --> 00:08:38,383
BATTLE OF KANEGASAKI

176
00:08:38,384 --> 00:08:39,385
All done.

177
00:08:41,387 --> 00:08:43,122
It turned out so powerful.

178
00:08:46,259 --> 00:08:48,761
What's happening in this scene?

179
00:08:50,963 --> 00:08:51,931
They're fighting.

180
00:08:54,267 --> 00:08:56,535
But they're getting pushed back
by the enemy.

181
00:08:56,536 --> 00:08:58,704
I see.

182
00:08:59,972 --> 00:09:00,806
Who's this?

183
00:09:02,074 --> 00:09:03,375
- Nobunaga.
- I thought so.

184
00:09:03,376 --> 00:09:04,809
He's so strong and amazing.

185
00:09:04,810 --> 00:09:05,845
Yeah, he's amazing.

186
00:09:12,919 --> 00:09:14,387
Hey, Tatsuki.

187
00:09:16,989 --> 00:09:19,392
Don't tell anyone
that I'm a history buff, okay?

188
00:09:20,626 --> 00:09:21,827
Okay.

189
00:09:36,342 --> 00:09:38,043
As for Thursday's Activity Day,

190
00:09:38,044 --> 00:09:39,911
we couldn't pick just one thing,

191
00:09:39,912 --> 00:09:41,479
so we'll be doing everything.

192
00:09:41,480 --> 00:09:42,914
It'll be like Sports Day.

193
00:09:42,915 --> 00:09:45,318
Then let's play tug-of-war too.

194
00:09:45,885 --> 00:09:48,820
I just got this rope. Look!

195
00:09:48,821 --> 00:09:50,689
No way!

196
00:09:50,690 --> 00:09:52,023
Where did you get that?

197
00:09:52,024 --> 00:09:53,625
Did you get it from a shrine?

198
00:09:53,626 --> 00:09:56,194
I guess it was being used
at the local festival,

199
00:09:56,195 --> 00:09:57,229
but it's too old now.

200
00:09:57,797 --> 00:10:00,266
- Then let's do tug-of-war too.
- Okay.

201
00:10:01,033 --> 00:10:03,435
- Pull this, Soya.
- Okay.

202
00:10:03,436 --> 00:10:04,270
Come on.

203
00:10:04,704 --> 00:10:05,538
‎Wow.

204
00:10:08,474 --> 00:10:11,010
‎-Bye Professor.
‎-Bye

205
00:10:13,946 --> 00:10:15,246
Hey there.

206
00:10:15,247 --> 00:10:16,548
Hey.

207
00:10:16,549 --> 00:10:18,150
- A collage?
- Yes.

208
00:10:19,352 --> 00:10:21,486
A Sengoku warlord and soccer players.

209
00:10:21,487 --> 00:10:23,356
It's an interesting combination, isn't it?

210
00:10:24,490 --> 00:10:25,958
Who made this collage?

211
00:10:26,559 --> 00:10:28,593
He's a boy in fifth grade.

212
00:10:28,594 --> 00:10:31,363
He seems to be good at studies and sports,
and has friends too.

213
00:10:31,364 --> 00:10:33,398
But he refuses to go to school, right?

214
00:10:33,399 --> 00:10:34,700
- Yes.
- Why?

215
00:10:37,503 --> 00:10:39,305
- He said it's a drag.
- A drag?

216
00:10:40,573 --> 00:10:42,907
Does that mean he finds it tiring?

217
00:10:42,908 --> 00:10:45,910
No, how can I explain it…?

218
00:10:45,911 --> 00:10:48,047
Is it that he can't sum up
the energy to go?

219
00:10:49,782 --> 00:10:51,884
I think he considers it a hassle.

220
00:10:52,885 --> 00:10:55,688
- I see.
- What do you think about this?

221
00:11:00,326 --> 00:11:02,727
There's just one guy who's running away.

222
00:11:02,728 --> 00:11:04,262
You're right.

223
00:11:04,263 --> 00:11:06,766
The boss has a really
intimidating presence, doesn't he?

224
00:11:07,867 --> 00:11:09,835
Does it represent someone?

225
00:11:10,536 --> 00:11:12,638
If it's not a friend,

226
00:11:13,305 --> 00:11:14,240
maybe

227
00:11:15,541 --> 00:11:17,076
a teacher, for example?

228
00:11:17,677 --> 00:11:19,010
That's a possibility.

229
00:11:19,011 --> 00:11:22,113
Kids sometimes stop going to school
when they don't get along with teachers.

230
00:11:22,114 --> 00:11:23,015
Yeah.

231
00:11:23,649 --> 00:11:26,051
Saku goes to Nishiogi Elementary School,

232
00:11:26,052 --> 00:11:28,753
so I'll try to find something out tomorrow

233
00:11:28,754 --> 00:11:30,989
when I go to submit
the academic progress report.

234
00:11:30,990 --> 00:11:32,424
You sure love schools, huh.

235
00:11:32,425 --> 00:11:34,592
It's not that I love it or anything.

236
00:11:34,593 --> 00:11:36,461
I hope you don't complicate things more.

237
00:11:36,462 --> 00:11:38,264
Then you want to just let things be?

238
00:11:40,399 --> 00:11:41,900
Tatsuki, you should go with her.

239
00:11:41,901 --> 00:11:44,603
- Oh, I can't tomorrow…
- You have plans?

240
00:11:45,771 --> 00:11:47,373
I have to catch
a different colored Pikachu.

241
00:11:47,940 --> 00:11:49,541
What?

242
00:11:49,542 --> 00:11:51,476
This is more important than that!

243
00:11:51,477 --> 00:11:52,845
I guess you can't cancel that.

244
00:11:54,080 --> 00:11:55,347
Are you serious?

245
00:11:56,248 --> 00:11:58,017
NISHIOGI ELEMENTARY SCHOOL

246
00:11:58,584 --> 00:12:01,186
I can't think of the reason why either.

247
00:12:01,187 --> 00:12:05,423
Sugitani is a very popular
and outgoing student in our class.

248
00:12:05,424 --> 00:12:07,960
He started missing school
around mid-April, right?

249
00:12:08,994 --> 00:12:10,662
At first it was just Mondays.

250
00:12:10,663 --> 00:12:13,999
Then Mondays and Wednesdays.
It gradually kept increasing.

251
00:12:14,567 --> 00:12:15,900
I see.

252
00:12:15,901 --> 00:12:16,868
Oh, sorry,

253
00:12:16,869 --> 00:12:19,104
- I have to practice for Sports Day.
- Sorry.

254
00:12:19,105 --> 00:12:21,073
- Thank you.
- No problem.

255
00:12:24,310 --> 00:12:25,410
CLASS SCHEDULE

256
00:12:25,411 --> 00:12:28,346
Mondays and Wednesdays.

257
00:12:28,347 --> 00:12:29,314
MONDAY - PE

258
00:12:29,315 --> 00:12:30,782
WEDNESDAY

259
00:12:30,783 --> 00:12:32,251
PE

260
00:12:34,754 --> 00:12:37,922
All right, stop. One, two.

261
00:12:37,923 --> 00:12:39,792
Hey, you stepped out of line.

262
00:12:40,359 --> 00:12:41,427
Let's do it one more time.

263
00:12:42,294 --> 00:12:43,962
Step in place.

264
00:12:43,963 --> 00:12:45,598
It looks like Sports Day is in two weeks.

265
00:12:46,699 --> 00:12:49,502
I wonder if there's any point
in practicing marching.

266
00:12:50,302 --> 00:12:52,438
It's satisfying to watch
when they're in sync, isn't it?

267
00:12:53,005 --> 00:12:54,540
- One, two.
- You think so?

268
00:12:55,741 --> 00:13:00,145
I wonder if Saku
didn't like the Sports Day practice.

269
00:13:00,146 --> 00:13:02,114
- But he's good at all sports, right?
- Yes.

270
00:13:02,848 --> 00:13:05,617
In that case, Sports Day is actually

271
00:13:05,618 --> 00:13:07,619
a great opportunity for him to shine.

272
00:13:07,620 --> 00:13:09,521
But he started skipping school on days

273
00:13:09,522 --> 00:13:11,055
when they had PE,

274
00:13:11,056 --> 00:13:12,992
and when the Sports Day practices began.

275
00:13:14,660 --> 00:13:16,828
Step in place.

276
00:13:16,829 --> 00:13:18,062
Doesn't that teacher

277
00:13:18,063 --> 00:13:21,199
- kind of remind you of Nobunaga?
- One, two.

278
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:23,368
One, two! Hey, you're doing it
the wrong way!

279
00:13:23,369 --> 00:13:26,437
One, two.
Keep looking at everyone around you!

280
00:13:26,438 --> 00:13:28,707
- Oh yes…
- One, two!

281
00:13:31,677 --> 00:13:34,779
Excuse me. Sorry to bother you
when you're so busy.

282
00:13:34,780 --> 00:13:37,716
I'm Aomine from
the alternative school, Yukanai.

283
00:13:39,151 --> 00:13:41,187
- I'm Tatsuki.
- How can I help you?

284
00:13:41,987 --> 00:13:45,391
I'd like to ask you a few questions
about Saku Sugitani.

285
00:13:47,092 --> 00:13:49,895
I'm very worried about Sugitani too.

286
00:13:50,462 --> 00:13:52,630
How is he doing at your school?

287
00:13:52,631 --> 00:13:55,466
Oh, he's doing well.

288
00:13:55,467 --> 00:13:57,468
I'm so glad.

289
00:13:57,469 --> 00:13:59,638
He was always so cheerful.

290
00:14:03,242 --> 00:14:05,109
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

291
00:14:05,110 --> 00:14:05,945
Good day.

292
00:14:08,514 --> 00:14:11,083
<i>He ended up being a nice guy, huh?</i>

293
00:14:11,650 --> 00:14:13,852
You shouldn't have judged
a book by its cover.

294
00:14:13,853 --> 00:14:16,554
Hey, you thought he was scary too,
didn't you?

295
00:14:16,555 --> 00:14:17,922
No, I did not.

296
00:14:17,923 --> 00:14:18,858
So unfair.

297
00:14:21,493 --> 00:14:25,029
I was absolutely convinced that
the Sports Day practice was the issue.

298
00:14:25,030 --> 00:14:26,531
I think you've got it right.

299
00:14:26,532 --> 00:14:28,033
You think so too?

300
00:14:29,235 --> 00:14:30,735
I got this.

301
00:14:30,736 --> 00:14:32,770
- The program for Sports Day?
- Yup.

302
00:14:32,771 --> 00:14:33,972
SPORTS DAY

303
00:14:33,973 --> 00:14:36,507
Which one was Saku planning
to participate in?

304
00:14:36,508 --> 00:14:40,812
He was chosen for the fifth-grade events,
and also as a runner for the relay team.

305
00:14:40,813 --> 00:14:41,913
I see.

306
00:14:41,914 --> 00:14:43,549
SPORTS DAY

307
00:14:47,920 --> 00:14:49,153
All right!

308
00:14:49,154 --> 00:14:51,356
- Damn it.
- He's so good.

309
00:14:51,357 --> 00:14:52,624
Saku, you're so good.

310
00:14:52,625 --> 00:14:53,726
What's the trick?

311
00:14:54,793 --> 00:14:57,929
Don't just move your arm,
but put your weight into it like this.

312
00:14:57,930 --> 00:15:00,966
- You're good at everything, Saku.
- Kind of.

313
00:15:01,600 --> 00:15:03,969
All right everyone.
Let's start cleaning up.

314
00:15:05,237 --> 00:15:06,905
- Okay.
- All right!

315
00:15:06,906 --> 00:15:09,207
- Good job.
- I did it.

316
00:15:09,208 --> 00:15:10,642
- I did it.
- You're a genius.

317
00:15:10,643 --> 00:15:11,876
I did it.

318
00:15:11,877 --> 00:15:12,977
Let's clean up.

319
00:15:12,978 --> 00:15:14,445
- No, one more time.
- Clean it up.

320
00:15:14,446 --> 00:15:15,947
Let's play this other game.

321
00:15:15,948 --> 00:15:17,482
- What?
- Let's play this game.

322
00:15:17,483 --> 00:15:19,150
I want to play Jenga.

323
00:15:19,151 --> 00:15:20,652
What about Dominion?

324
00:15:20,653 --> 00:15:22,287
Let's all clean up.

325
00:15:22,288 --> 00:15:24,555
Everyone please take
the Activity Day flyer

326
00:15:24,556 --> 00:15:26,357
when you leave.

327
00:15:26,358 --> 00:15:29,327
- Okay.
- Is Tatsuki going too?

328
00:15:29,328 --> 00:15:31,463
Yeah. You'll be going too, right?

329
00:15:32,031 --> 00:15:33,865
Yeah, I'm looking forward to it.

330
00:15:33,866 --> 00:15:35,466
Take this home with you.

331
00:15:35,467 --> 00:15:36,935
Thank you.

332
00:15:36,936 --> 00:15:40,471
- Oh, wow, how exciting.
- Take this home with you.

333
00:15:40,472 --> 00:15:41,806
- Thanks.
- Take care.

334
00:15:41,807 --> 00:15:43,642
- Bye.
- Bye.

335
00:15:47,680 --> 00:15:50,382
- Go Red!
- Game start!

336
00:15:51,784 --> 00:15:53,318
‎-Gaku!
‎-Tatsuki!

337
00:15:53,319 --> 00:15:54,787
Nice pass!

338
00:16:02,594 --> 00:16:04,797
Go, go!

339
00:16:07,232 --> 00:16:08,534
Start.

340
00:16:10,636 --> 00:16:12,071
‎We can do it.

341
00:16:16,041 --> 00:16:17,742
Make sure you score.

342
00:16:17,743 --> 00:16:20,278
- You can do it, Tatsuki.
- Go.

343
00:16:20,279 --> 00:16:21,180
Go!

344
00:16:34,960 --> 00:16:37,162
Don't get too depressed about it.

345
00:16:55,014 --> 00:16:56,015
Saku.

346
00:16:57,683 --> 00:16:58,684
You're not going to dance?

347
00:17:01,653 --> 00:17:05,356
<i>If they try to go into defense here,
then that will cause…</i>

348
00:17:05,357 --> 00:17:06,492
- Tatsuki.
- Yeah?

349
00:17:07,693 --> 00:17:09,328
Was it okay for you to leave?

350
00:17:10,462 --> 00:17:11,630
The truth is,

351
00:17:12,131 --> 00:17:14,199
I'm not very good at ball games.

352
00:17:15,434 --> 00:17:16,702
My penalty kick was terrible, huh?

353
00:17:17,369 --> 00:17:18,669
Yeah.

354
00:17:18,670 --> 00:17:20,005
I lost motivation after that.

355
00:17:20,606 --> 00:17:22,407
If I did something that embarrassing

356
00:17:22,408 --> 00:17:23,809
- I wouldn't be able to live.
- Hey.

357
00:17:25,878 --> 00:17:29,248
I'm not like you who can do everything.

358
00:17:35,020 --> 00:17:37,823
I can't dance.

359
00:17:41,360 --> 00:17:42,428
I see.

360
00:17:43,695 --> 00:17:45,130
I can't do the dance

361
00:17:46,665 --> 00:17:47,833
for Sports Day.

362
00:17:48,333 --> 00:17:52,136
One, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight.

363
00:17:52,137 --> 00:17:54,906
One, two, three, four, five, six…

364
00:17:54,907 --> 00:17:56,642
<i>I can never remember the steps.</i>

365
00:17:58,143 --> 00:17:59,244
<i>Once I fall out of sync,</i>

366
00:17:59,878 --> 00:18:01,547
<i>I can't keep up anymore.</i>

367
00:18:03,982 --> 00:18:05,951
I just keep feeling
more and more pathetic.

368
00:18:10,622 --> 00:18:11,824
I see.

369
00:18:13,592 --> 00:18:15,060
That's tough.

370
00:18:26,939 --> 00:18:28,707
Just ask to be removed from the dance.

371
00:18:29,475 --> 00:18:30,309
What?

372
00:18:31,009 --> 00:18:32,478
No need to force yourself to do it.

373
00:18:35,948 --> 00:18:37,449
Everyone has to participate in the dance.

374
00:18:38,016 --> 00:18:40,486
But you still want to compete
in the other events, right?

375
00:18:41,053 --> 00:18:43,489
Isn't it frustrating to have to sit
everything out just for that?

376
00:18:51,096 --> 00:18:52,331
If you want to run away,

377
00:18:53,232 --> 00:18:54,366
it's okay to do so.

378
00:18:55,834 --> 00:18:58,203
I just ran away too.

379
00:19:02,975 --> 00:19:04,009
But…

380
00:19:05,944 --> 00:19:08,447
I can't admit to everyone now
that I'm bad at dancing.

381
00:19:10,816 --> 00:19:12,951
Because you're known for
being good at everything?

382
00:19:16,321 --> 00:19:17,222
Yeah.

383
00:19:25,631 --> 00:19:26,565
What do you want to do?

384
00:19:29,835 --> 00:19:32,404
You can choose to do
whatever you want, Saku.

385
00:19:48,854 --> 00:19:49,855
I don't want…

386
00:19:56,061 --> 00:19:57,296
to do the dance.

387
00:20:10,409 --> 00:20:11,642
I went to his school.

388
00:20:11,643 --> 00:20:14,246
They said Saku doesn't have
to participate in the dance.

389
00:20:18,784 --> 00:20:22,253
Um… I actually went out of my way
to visit his school

390
00:20:22,254 --> 00:20:24,122
after Activity Day ended.

391
00:20:25,290 --> 00:20:26,358
Thanks.

392
00:20:27,759 --> 00:20:29,928
I'm glad you can benefit
from my love for school.

393
00:20:34,866 --> 00:20:35,934
What?

394
00:20:37,769 --> 00:20:40,806
I'm sure schools love you too,
Ms. Shizuku.

395
00:20:42,107 --> 00:20:43,208
Forget it.

396
00:20:45,811 --> 00:20:48,313
Thank you. I'll relay the news to Saku.

397
00:20:49,581 --> 00:20:51,783
Thank you. Bye.

398
00:21:11,737 --> 00:21:13,037
Good morning.

399
00:21:13,038 --> 00:21:14,705
Hey, Saku.

400
00:21:14,706 --> 00:21:16,775
Saku is here. Let's play Ruler Wars.

401
00:21:18,543 --> 00:21:20,312
- Yeah, let's.
- Are you better now?

402
00:21:21,246 --> 00:21:23,714
Yup. I made a complete recovery!

403
00:21:23,715 --> 00:21:27,285
Right, left, hop, hop, hop.

404
00:21:27,286 --> 00:21:30,821
One, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight.

405
00:21:30,822 --> 00:21:32,924
Hey, did you make your mask?

406
00:21:33,492 --> 00:21:36,327
- A mask?
- All right, let's take a break.

407
00:21:36,328 --> 00:21:38,229
- No…
- Make sure to stay hydrated.

408
00:21:38,230 --> 00:21:41,232
I'm going to the restroom.

409
00:21:41,233 --> 00:21:44,269
Hey Saku. Why are you just watching?

410
00:21:46,705 --> 00:21:47,539
Just because…

411
00:21:49,107 --> 00:21:50,142
I'm going to the restroom.

412
00:21:54,112 --> 00:21:57,883
Left, right, left, hop…

413
00:22:13,665 --> 00:22:15,666
YUKANAI
NOW ACCEPTING NEW STUDENTS!

414
00:22:15,667 --> 00:22:19,404
Yes, Saku is here, so please don't worry.

415
00:22:19,971 --> 00:22:23,008
Yes. Goodbye.

416
00:22:23,809 --> 00:22:25,409
- Was that his school?
- Yeah,

417
00:22:25,410 --> 00:22:27,479
it seems like he suddenly left
during PE.

418
00:22:30,115 --> 00:22:31,483
I see.

419
00:22:41,860 --> 00:22:43,995
You left school without telling anyone?

420
00:22:47,199 --> 00:22:48,166
It's boring to just watch.

421
00:22:48,800 --> 00:22:50,469
Yeah, it's boring, huh?

422
00:22:51,570 --> 00:22:53,672
But if you leave without a word,
everyone will worry.

423
00:22:54,506 --> 00:22:55,640
I'm sorry.

424
00:22:56,508 --> 00:22:58,110
Want to make another collage?

425
00:23:01,646 --> 00:23:03,415
- I have to return the books I borrowed.
- What?

426
00:23:04,149 --> 00:23:06,250
Oh, you can have those old books.

427
00:23:06,251 --> 00:23:07,452
But I read them all.

428
00:23:13,024 --> 00:23:15,527
LET'S MAKE A MASK FOR THE DANCE!

429
00:23:17,529 --> 00:23:19,464
Apparently, it's a mask for the dance.

430
00:23:22,467 --> 00:23:23,301
I don't need that.

431
00:23:30,175 --> 00:23:31,042
Want to make it?

432
00:23:32,010 --> 00:23:32,844
What?

433
00:23:35,714 --> 00:23:38,650
- He sat out on practice, but left mid-way?
- Yes.

434
00:23:39,151 --> 00:23:41,886
But we're not really sure why.

435
00:23:41,887 --> 00:23:44,956
Maybe he started hating himself
for running away.

436
00:23:46,258 --> 00:23:48,193
That's a possibility too.

437
00:23:48,760 --> 00:23:52,597
He tends to be a perfectionist.

438
00:23:53,899 --> 00:23:56,233
Since I used to work
as a middle school teacher,

439
00:23:56,234 --> 00:23:58,536
I tend to think that
you have to challenge all things,

440
00:23:58,537 --> 00:24:01,472
even if it's something you're not
particularly good at.

441
00:24:01,473 --> 00:24:02,441
Yes.

442
00:24:03,108 --> 00:24:07,112
I think overcoming difficulties
is also a part of education.

443
00:24:08,647 --> 00:24:12,683
But if it's going to break their spirit,
then it's better

444
00:24:12,684 --> 00:24:14,486
not to push them too hard.

445
00:24:17,289 --> 00:24:19,357
It's tough, isn't it?

446
00:24:22,627 --> 00:24:25,263
- Done.
- Let me see.

447
00:24:25,864 --> 00:24:27,698
Ta-da. Guess who this is.

448
00:24:27,699 --> 00:24:28,899
A hint. He's a soccer player.

449
00:24:28,900 --> 00:24:30,235
I wonder who it is.

450
00:24:32,204 --> 00:24:33,270
Ramos.

451
00:24:33,271 --> 00:24:35,207
- Who is that?
- You don't know Ramos?

452
00:24:35,774 --> 00:24:38,243
Seriously? Okay then…

453
00:24:40,745 --> 00:24:42,112
Is it Messi?

454
00:24:42,113 --> 00:24:43,781
- Bingo.
- Yes.

455
00:24:43,782 --> 00:24:44,649
Let's see yours.

456
00:24:46,818 --> 00:24:47,986
Ta-da.

457
00:24:49,421 --> 00:24:50,955
It looks just like you.

458
00:24:50,956 --> 00:24:52,123
Right?

459
00:24:52,958 --> 00:24:55,026
Let's draw on the other side too.

460
00:24:55,694 --> 00:24:56,961
- The other side?
- Yeah.

461
00:24:56,962 --> 00:24:59,064
For the other side…

462
00:24:59,998 --> 00:25:03,435
Let's draw a secret side of us,
one we usually never show anyone.

463
00:25:12,844 --> 00:25:14,012
Are you crying?

464
00:25:15,881 --> 00:25:18,683
You usually don't want anyone
to see you crying, right?

465
00:25:23,054 --> 00:25:26,124
Is that a Sengoku warlord?

466
00:25:26,925 --> 00:25:28,325
Nobunaga?

467
00:25:28,326 --> 00:25:29,493
Bingo.

468
00:25:29,494 --> 00:25:30,795
Why did you choose Nobunaga?

469
00:25:34,032 --> 00:25:35,100
I wonder why.

470
00:25:38,970 --> 00:25:40,939
Oh, because it's a secret
that you're a history buff?

471
00:25:42,207 --> 00:25:44,709
Maybe that's it.
After all, it doesn't fit my image.

472
00:25:47,112 --> 00:25:48,680
Both the front and back turned out great.

473
00:25:52,050 --> 00:25:54,619
Saku, let's head home.

474
00:25:58,290 --> 00:26:00,058
It's okay. I'll clean up. You can go.

475
00:26:00,859 --> 00:26:01,760
- Thanks.
- Sure.

476
00:26:13,204 --> 00:26:14,673
- Tatsuki.
- Yeah?

477
00:26:18,209 --> 00:26:19,177
I'm going

478
00:26:20,445 --> 00:26:21,613
to try the dance after all.

479
00:26:22,581 --> 00:26:23,480
What?

480
00:26:23,481 --> 00:26:25,283
I'll practice on my own

481
00:26:26,651 --> 00:26:27,986
and learn the dance by Sports Day.

482
00:26:32,157 --> 00:26:32,991
Okay.

483
00:26:45,403 --> 00:26:46,904
- A mask?
- Yeah.

484
00:26:46,905 --> 00:26:50,074
He made the mask
that's going to be used for the dance,

485
00:26:50,075 --> 00:26:52,643
but it seems
that really got him motivated.

486
00:26:52,644 --> 00:26:54,079
What kind of a mask was it?

487
00:26:54,846 --> 00:26:57,248
Messi is on the front,
and Nobunaga is on the back.

488
00:26:58,216 --> 00:26:59,917
Apparently, Saku admires both of them.

489
00:26:59,918 --> 00:27:01,419
I see.

490
00:27:02,120 --> 00:27:03,888
This is Mr. Tatsuki's mask.

491
00:27:04,723 --> 00:27:05,924
Don't bring that out…

492
00:27:07,726 --> 00:27:09,526
Oh? Why is he crying?

493
00:27:09,527 --> 00:27:10,795
Well,

494
00:27:11,596 --> 00:27:13,664
it's a face I don't want to show others.

495
00:27:13,665 --> 00:27:15,600
I see.

496
00:27:16,501 --> 00:27:18,235
When doing art therapy,

497
00:27:18,236 --> 00:27:20,071
people create pieces
that distinguish between

498
00:27:20,705 --> 00:27:24,509
their outward self and the self
they wish to keep hidden deep inside.

499
00:27:27,178 --> 00:27:28,013
Huh?

500
00:27:28,647 --> 00:27:30,547
Mr. Tatsuki,

501
00:27:30,548 --> 00:27:32,850
- what are you keeping hidden inside?
- Stop that.

502
00:27:32,851 --> 00:27:36,254
By the way,
can you stop calling me "Mr." please?

503
00:27:36,988 --> 00:27:38,122
It seems like

504
00:27:38,123 --> 00:27:40,624
art therapy really does work, doesn't it?

505
00:27:40,625 --> 00:27:42,627
Saku seems to have been motivated.

506
00:27:43,328 --> 00:27:44,329
What do you think?

507
00:27:45,964 --> 00:27:50,167
But perhaps
even he himself doesn't realize

508
00:27:50,168 --> 00:27:52,704
the true feelings he has
deep within his heart.

509
00:27:53,338 --> 00:27:54,673
I see.

510
00:27:55,240 --> 00:27:58,475
If I recall correctly, he used Nobunaga
in that collage the other day too.

511
00:27:58,476 --> 00:28:02,780
I was under the impression
that he was a frightening figure to Saku,

512
00:28:02,781 --> 00:28:04,115
but he actually seems to like him.

513
00:28:04,849 --> 00:28:08,185
In that case, you ought to delve deeper

514
00:28:08,186 --> 00:28:10,588
into the thing that he likes.

515
00:28:11,923 --> 00:28:13,858
You just might discover something new.

516
00:28:15,226 --> 00:28:16,227
Okay.

517
00:28:17,495 --> 00:28:20,999
<i>Right, left, hop, hop, hop.</i>

518
00:28:32,444 --> 00:28:35,814
<i>Ready? Let's start.</i>

519
00:28:36,514 --> 00:28:39,851
<i>Five, six, seven, eight.
One, two, three, four…</i>

520
00:29:38,977 --> 00:29:42,847
Three, four, five, six…

521
00:29:46,785 --> 00:29:48,419
Let's do it again.

522
00:29:51,990 --> 00:29:53,191
YUKANAI

523
00:29:58,596 --> 00:29:59,697
Good morning, Saku.

524
00:30:03,768 --> 00:30:04,602
Where's Tatsuki?

525
00:30:05,403 --> 00:30:06,538
- I'll go call him.
- No…

526
00:30:09,207 --> 00:30:10,041
It's okay.

527
00:30:20,919 --> 00:30:21,853
What're you doing?

528
00:30:25,190 --> 00:30:27,324
I'm not very good with history,

529
00:30:27,325 --> 00:30:30,562
so I tried to study by putting myself
in Nobunaga’s shoes. I splurged on this.

530
00:30:31,896 --> 00:30:32,730
You bought it?

531
00:30:36,601 --> 00:30:39,037
By the way, Lord, what is the matter?

532
00:30:50,548 --> 00:30:51,382
We have

533
00:30:52,784 --> 00:30:55,786
a full dance rehearsal
this afternoon, but…

534
00:30:55,787 --> 00:30:57,789
Sports Day is coming up, huh?

535
00:31:00,291 --> 00:31:01,526
I'm scared.

536
00:31:02,293 --> 00:31:03,595
You practiced, right?

537
00:31:04,562 --> 00:31:05,396
But

538
00:31:05,997 --> 00:31:07,364
I've only practiced on my own.

539
00:31:07,365 --> 00:31:10,301
It might be hard
to dance along with everyone, huh?

540
00:31:12,036 --> 00:31:13,104
That's what scares me.

541
00:31:14,639 --> 00:31:15,874
Do you want to sit out?

542
00:31:17,709 --> 00:31:19,376
You can run away if you want.

543
00:31:19,377 --> 00:31:22,280
But that just doesn't fit my image.

544
00:31:23,281 --> 00:31:24,449
I’m supposed to be strong

545
00:31:25,116 --> 00:31:26,651
and able to do anything.

546
00:31:28,086 --> 00:31:29,020
Why?

547
00:31:31,055 --> 00:31:31,990
Why?

548
00:31:35,059 --> 00:31:35,960
If I can't do it,

549
00:31:37,395 --> 00:31:38,930
everyone will be disappointed in me.

550
00:31:40,632 --> 00:31:41,966
I'll look lame too.

551
00:31:44,702 --> 00:31:46,437
That's just not who I am.

552
00:31:47,572 --> 00:31:48,473
That's why

553
00:31:49,374 --> 00:31:52,176
you have to be strong like Nobunaga?

554
00:31:54,545 --> 00:31:55,413
Yeah.

555
00:32:00,051 --> 00:32:01,586
But apparently,

556
00:32:02,253 --> 00:32:04,289
Nobunaga actually ran away
from a battle once.

557
00:32:08,927 --> 00:32:12,095
This image of Nobunaga
that you pasted on here,

558
00:32:12,096 --> 00:32:15,065
was taken from an illustration
of the Battle of Kanegasaki, huh?

559
00:32:15,066 --> 00:32:16,033
BATTLE OF KANEGASAKI

560
00:32:16,034 --> 00:32:17,969
I figured that out yesterday
after studying.

561
00:32:19,003 --> 00:32:20,505
I didn't even notice that.

562
00:32:21,272 --> 00:32:23,473
The Battle of Kanegasaki is referred to as

563
00:32:23,474 --> 00:32:25,677
the "battle of the forced retreat",
isn't it?

564
00:32:30,181 --> 00:32:31,782
In 1570,

565
00:32:31,783 --> 00:32:34,818
Nobunaga laid siege to Kanegasaki Castle,

566
00:32:34,819 --> 00:32:36,487
but after being betrayed by Azai Nagamasa,

567
00:32:37,055 --> 00:32:38,656
he had to flee in order to survive.

568
00:32:40,058 --> 00:32:41,693
What do you think

569
00:32:42,260 --> 00:32:44,262
of Nobunaga for retreating? Was he lame?

570
00:32:46,998 --> 00:32:47,966
If it was me

571
00:32:48,733 --> 00:32:49,834
I'd be a bit embarrassed.

572
00:32:51,469 --> 00:32:52,769
I see.

573
00:32:52,770 --> 00:32:53,604
But

574
00:32:55,106 --> 00:32:56,207
I don't think

575
00:32:57,375 --> 00:32:58,209
he's lame.

576
00:33:02,013 --> 00:33:04,047
It's kind of cool

577
00:33:04,048 --> 00:33:05,883
how he bares all his weaknesses, huh?

578
00:33:23,234 --> 00:33:24,535
Saku, you can become

579
00:33:25,503 --> 00:33:26,571
Nobunaga too.

580
00:34:59,263 --> 00:35:01,398
Saku, let's play soccer.

581
00:35:01,399 --> 00:35:02,866
- Let's go.
- Let's play.

582
00:35:02,867 --> 00:35:03,701
Wait.

583
00:35:05,736 --> 00:35:06,671
Sorry.

584
00:35:09,107 --> 00:35:11,342
Can you help me practice the dance?

585
00:35:13,678 --> 00:35:16,447
I couldn't get all the moves
by watching the video.

586
00:35:19,150 --> 00:35:20,283
Sure.

587
00:35:20,284 --> 00:35:21,152
He took days off.

588
00:35:21,719 --> 00:35:22,820
Yeah, so we'll help you.

589
00:35:23,821 --> 00:35:24,689
Thanks.

590
00:35:25,223 --> 00:35:27,624
Right, left,

591
00:35:27,625 --> 00:35:29,426
down, and tap.

592
00:35:29,427 --> 00:35:31,895
Get up.

593
00:35:31,896 --> 00:35:34,764
Touch and turn. Right…

594
00:35:34,765 --> 00:35:36,567
- Sorry, one more time.
- Sure.

595
00:35:37,168 --> 00:35:38,536
Let's review the previous moves too.

596
00:35:41,806 --> 00:35:42,840
What's the matter?

597
00:35:44,075 --> 00:35:44,909
Hey,

598
00:35:46,110 --> 00:35:48,179
what do you think of me
being a bad dancer?

599
00:35:48,980 --> 00:35:49,947
Why this all of a sudden?

600
00:35:50,781 --> 00:35:52,150
I have no sense of rhythm,

601
00:35:53,184 --> 00:35:54,552
and I'm stiff…

602
00:35:56,554 --> 00:35:57,522
Isn't that lame?

603
00:35:58,656 --> 00:35:59,690
Not really.

604
00:36:01,192 --> 00:36:03,227
But I'm known as someone
who can do anything.

605
00:36:03,828 --> 00:36:04,662
Huh?

606
00:36:05,630 --> 00:36:07,831
- Is that right?
- What?

607
00:36:07,832 --> 00:36:10,500
We don't think you're perfect or anything.

608
00:36:10,501 --> 00:36:11,768
Yeah.

609
00:36:11,769 --> 00:36:13,270
- What?
- Yeah,

610
00:36:13,271 --> 00:36:15,705
because you can be pretty kooky.

611
00:36:15,706 --> 00:36:16,874
Yeah, totally.

612
00:36:18,042 --> 00:36:19,910
No way. Kooky? Me?

613
00:36:19,911 --> 00:36:21,645
For example,

614
00:36:21,646 --> 00:36:25,282
when it was music class,
you went to the home economics room.

615
00:36:25,283 --> 00:36:29,252
First of all, the fact
that you think you're perfect…

616
00:36:29,253 --> 00:36:30,087
Means you're kooky.

617
00:36:31,455 --> 00:36:32,356
Seriously?

618
00:36:33,658 --> 00:36:35,825
That's how I was coming across
to everyone?

619
00:36:35,826 --> 00:36:38,996
But you guys haven't figured out
that I'm a history buff, right?

620
00:36:43,434 --> 00:36:45,936
- Who cares if everyone knows?
- Yeah.

621
00:36:45,937 --> 00:36:47,037
By the way,

622
00:36:47,038 --> 00:36:49,307
let's practice, or you'll really be lame.

623
00:36:50,441 --> 00:36:52,776
Sorry, can we start from the top again?

624
00:36:52,777 --> 00:36:53,677
Okay.

625
00:36:53,678 --> 00:36:55,579
- Ready?
- Yeah.

626
00:36:55,580 --> 00:36:57,280
Let's start.

627
00:36:57,281 --> 00:37:00,750
One, two, three, four…

628
00:37:00,751 --> 00:37:03,453
Walk in place. Begin.

629
00:37:03,454 --> 00:37:04,888
One, two.

630
00:37:04,889 --> 00:37:07,991
Next up is a dance performance
by the fifth graders.

631
00:37:07,992 --> 00:37:10,260
It's called, "Dancing

632
00:37:10,261 --> 00:37:11,262
As My Character."

633
00:37:12,296 --> 00:37:13,496
- Where is he?
- I see him.

634
00:37:13,497 --> 00:37:15,199
Where? Point to him.

635
00:37:15,933 --> 00:37:17,367
- Oh, there he is.
- That's him.

636
00:37:17,368 --> 00:37:18,568
Good luck.

637
00:37:18,569 --> 00:37:19,469
Oh.

638
00:37:19,470 --> 00:37:20,404
Hello.

639
00:37:21,305 --> 00:37:24,407
- Hello.
- Saku is over there.

640
00:37:24,408 --> 00:37:26,776
- Oh, I see him. Thank you.
- He's Messi.

641
00:37:26,777 --> 00:37:27,945
One, two.

642
00:39:54,725 --> 00:39:56,494
Saku!

643
00:39:59,063 --> 00:40:00,398
You can do it!

644
00:40:05,136 --> 00:40:06,003
Tatsuki.

645
00:40:33,798 --> 00:40:35,199
‎All right.

646
00:41:37,895 --> 00:41:38,896
Good job!

647
00:42:40,524 --> 00:42:41,458
Tatsuki.

648
00:42:44,295 --> 00:42:45,262
You came.

649
00:42:46,230 --> 00:42:47,197
Good job.

650
00:42:47,932 --> 00:42:49,233
I messed up.

651
00:42:50,734 --> 00:42:52,169
But it was very you, Saku.

652
00:42:52,736 --> 00:42:53,971
What's that supposed to mean?

653
00:42:55,005 --> 00:42:56,340
You were cool,

654
00:42:57,374 --> 00:42:58,375
but also endearing.

655
00:42:59,543 --> 00:43:00,444
That's not my image.

656
00:43:01,512 --> 00:43:03,314
But I'll go with a new image from now on.

657
00:43:04,949 --> 00:43:08,319
But don't get tied down by your image.
It's fine for you to be yourself.

658
00:43:14,625 --> 00:43:16,426
But you're maintaining your image too.

659
00:43:16,427 --> 00:43:17,627
What?

660
00:43:17,628 --> 00:43:19,463
On the surface, you're always smiling

661
00:43:20,230 --> 00:43:22,166
but inside, there's darkness, right?

662
00:43:25,669 --> 00:43:27,370
I don't have a hidden side.

663
00:43:27,371 --> 00:43:29,005
There's definitely darkness to you.

664
00:43:29,006 --> 00:43:30,474
- You think so?
- Yeah.

665
00:43:31,241 --> 00:43:33,843
No need to force a smile
when you're feeling down.

666
00:43:33,844 --> 00:43:35,311
What the hell?

667
00:43:35,312 --> 00:43:36,480
Can I go visit you again?

668
00:43:37,047 --> 00:43:38,381
Of course.

669
00:43:38,382 --> 00:43:39,216
Bye.

670
00:43:40,150 --> 00:43:41,051
Bye.

671
00:43:41,919 --> 00:43:44,488
- See you.
- Bye.

672
00:44:17,121 --> 00:44:20,290
<i>Sora, staying holed up like that
isn't going to solve anything, is it?</i>

673
00:44:20,991 --> 00:44:21,825
Are you listening?

674
00:44:23,360 --> 00:44:24,894
- Sora.
- That's enough.

675
00:44:24,895 --> 00:44:27,598
- Go to work.
- Sora, open the door.

676
00:44:29,800 --> 00:44:31,701
- Come out here.
- No.

677
00:44:31,702 --> 00:44:34,371
Stop it. That's enough. Just stop it.

678
00:44:35,906 --> 00:44:36,740
Sora!

679
00:45:02,966 --> 00:45:04,534
PREVIEW OF THE NEXT EPISODE

680
00:45:04,535 --> 00:45:05,601
THIS DRAMA IS FICTION

681
00:45:05,602 --> 00:45:06,904
Subtitle translation by: Lili Morita
